title: Thousands march in Vienna against annual ‘far-right’ ball (PHOTOS, VIDEOS)
text:
Thousands march in Vienna against annual ‘far-right’ ball (PHOTOS, VIDEOS)  58 Get short URL Vienna, Austria, February 3, 2016 © Heinz-Peter Bader / Reuters Several thousand people have joined the protests against the annual so called Academics Ball in the Austrian capital of Vienna, sponsored by the right-wing Freedom Party. Smaller that last year’s, the rally passed peacefully under the watchful eye of police. 
Nearly 3,000 people marched through the city center, according the police estimations, the Austrian Nachrichten reported. 
Some 2,700 police officers were deployed to ensure security at the rally, Heute reports . — christopher glanzl (@tschoka23) February 3, 2017 
The organizers, however, say that at least 4,000 people turned up at the demonstration in the evening hour with strong support from the “Offensive against right” (OGR) antifascist movement. Фото опубликовано neuwal (@neuwal) Фев 3 2017 в 10:12 PST 
The year's protest drew a smaller crowd compared to last year's event when more than 5,000 people joined the protests, according to police estimates. Last year, organizers also disputed the numbers putting the figure at 8,000 demonstrators. Фото опубликовано neuwal (@neuwal) Фев 3 2017 в 9:41 PST 
Protesters could be seen carrying drums, flags and placards targeting the ball as well as Austria's authorities and especially Interior Minister Wolfgang Sobotka, who has called for restrictions on the right of gatherings.
